\par Remind me to fully address my system of semi-permanent death, though here's an intro: Players have a }{\f1\fs20\insrsid4018556 queue}{\f1\fs20\insrsid11354062  of "deaths" to rack up where they are resurrected by NPC means, though in an ic manner. 
Once that }{\f1\fs20\insrsid4018556 queue}{\f1\fs20\insrsid11354062  is done, they depend upon other player characters to bring them back. PCs can also be brought back in the meantime by other PCs, which would not count against their }{
\f1\fs20\insrsid4018556 queue}{\f1\fs20\insrsid11354062 . This means that characters die and end their stories, they are not immor
tal, they depend upon their religion or their resurrection skills [which some have], their enemies ic are well and truly their enemies, while their }{\f1\fs20\insrsid4018556 allies}{\f1\fs20\insrsid11354062 
